task.summary: Use resources to load feature files

Add more cases:
Steps with parameters, steps without parameters, steps defined in multiple files
Add test to check hooks are invoked
Add test for missing step definitions
Better name for test with hooks
Encapsulate success of compilation in successfullyGeneratedTestClasses
Use correct placeholders in statement generation
Extract target package name as val

Copy test resources to build folder
This is to ensure that tests run correctly also on Android Studio and IntellijIDEA without enabling delegation of run to gradle.
Add utilities files to publish and archive in s3
Add common maven group in root maven properties
Use simpler version of including dependencies.gradle from root
Generate all steps except non defined ones in non-strict mode

Apply pickle plugin in a better way
What's better I can't tell, but we had problems with the previous approach in the android client app and this did the trick, inspired by ButterKnife
Use correct hardcoded class for plugin
Use annotation via class instead of name
Support non alphanumeric chars in scenario names
Support non alphanumeric chars in scenario and feature names
Increase the number of spaces so it's clear they're intended
Add correct copyright holder to license
Add RunWith annotation to generated classes
